12:
Ha! Hahaha, I knew it! Your powers
got weaker too!
18:
Aww, look at him. After all that
sucking up he did to Tohru, he got
left behind.
20:
You know what? We'll take you in
instead! It's our turn to use you for
once!
29:
"Please, can we borrow your power?
We'll never get strong without you."
32:
If you'd put it like that, I might have
considered it.
35:
For a whiny little brat, you've got a
lot of guts...
37:
It's time someone taught you to
respect your superiors!
41:
They're like rats... coming out of the
woodworks with no end...
45:
Thinking they've got the run of
things... when they're powerless
without numbers...
51:
I've had enough... What's the point?
It's all over now anyway—
59:
Can't believe we've gotta take those
Aegis brats in. There's no way they're
gonna come quietly—
63:
Stupid tiger monster... It just had to
be you, didn't it?!
70:
I didn't lose back then... It didn't
count! There's no way I could've lost!
74:
Dragonlings! Dragonlings, to me!
Take him down!
77:
Damn it... Why can't you idiots... just
leave me—
87:
Hurk... You reek! When's the last time
you bathed?!
97:
...You've gotta be kidding me. Alk's
never gonna let me live this down...
113:
Why the hell did you throw me into
the bath?!
117:
You serious? You stink so bad you're
frying my sense of smell! Now get
scrubbing, and wash your clothes
while you're at it!
131:
You seem like you haven't eaten in a
while, so Alk made you some food—
138:
Taking pity on your enemy and
giving them charity. Must be nice to
feed your superiority complex.
145:
What, you want to wallow in your
misery? Is that it?
151: Oh, get off your high horse!
156:
Yeah, yeah, yell all you want. I'm not
taking the bait.
159:
You're practically starving, but you
still won't eat, huh? Are you really
that desperate for a reason to give
in?
162:
Just consider it stealing from us. Or
a debt, even. Whatever makes you
feel better.
165:
...Or is that also something you can't
decide for yourself?
169:
...We'll take our leave for now. You
should eat.
177:
A bit... He seems like he needs
looking after.
180:
Maybe, but I dunno if he'll want to
stay in Starview.
184:
That's not the reaction I expected
out of you.
188:
Well... I don't want to force him to do
anything he doesn't want to, you
know?
195:
Besides, Nimbus is the one that
brought him home. He should take
responsibility for him.
200:
The kid should be responsible for
himself.
203:
That's fair. But I know you're going to
do something anyway.
207:
...Listen, someone's gotta make sure
he starts cleaning up after his own
mess.
233:
You wanna know what real strength
is? It's not pretending you've got no
weaknesses...
237:
It's getting up and fighting no
matter how many times life knocks
you down!
249:
Him and his stupid friends and this
stupid place... All of it!
